    # Overview
    2
    3
    This project uses Machine Learning (ML) to make predictions on a binary classification target for a telecommunications company. The information came from a dataset provided on kaggle from SyriaTel. Models are used to make the best predictions to find out why customers have churned.(left the company)

    1  Overview

    This project uses Machine Learning (ML) to make predictions on a binary classification target for a telecommunications company. The information came from a dataset provided on kaggle from SyriaTel. Models are used to make the best predictions to find out why customers have churned.(left the company)

    xxxxxxxxxx
    3
     
    1
    # Business Problem
    2
    3
    SyriaTel wants to reduce the amount of money lost by checking what are the factors that have made consumers churn. This analysis can help predict which customers have the possibility of churning and find a way to retain them for the future.

    2  Business Problem

    SyriaTel wants to reduce the amount of money lost by checking what are the factors that have made consumers churn. This analysis can help predict which customers have the possibility of churning and find a way to retain them for the future.

    ## Summary for EDA

    3.1  Summary for EDA

    In [21]:
    xxxxxxxxxx
     
    1
    """
    2
    3
    There is some interesting information during the EDA process. We noticed that for the most part, the data was pretty clean.
    4
    There was not missing information data that needed to be imputed or dropped. For the most part, a lot of the data seems to be
    5
    evenly distributed as well.
    6
    7
    We also noticed that the data is heavily imbalanced with a false churn of about 86% to the 14% true churn. It will be extremely
    8
    important to balance the data later during modeling to make sure that the model does not skew towards mainly toward
    9
    the majority class.
    10
    11
    Some binary data did have to converted into numeric data but does not affect data leakage since there were no transformations
    12
    to the data.
    13
    14
    There were also some insights on churn based on states. They were categorized into high churn, mid churn states and low churn
    15
    states. That may be something to take into consideration for the company when making decisions on where to pursue action
    16
    after the models effectively predict churn.
    17
    18
    19
    """
    executed in 3ms, finished 10:36:16 2022-07-15
    Out[21]:
    '\n\nThere is some interesting information during the EDA process. We noticed that for the most part, the data was pretty clean. \nThere was not missing information data that needed to be imputed or dropped. For the most part, a lot of the data seems to be \nevenly distributed as well.\n\nWe also noticed that the data is heavily imbalanced with a false churn of about 86% to the 14% true churn. It will be extremely\nimportant to balance the data later during modeling to make sure that the model does not skew towards mainly toward\nthe majority class.\n\nSome binary data did have to converted into numeric data but does not affect data leakage since there were no transformations \nto the data.\n\nThere were also some insights on churn based on states. They were categorized into high churn, mid churn states and low churn \nstates. That may be something to take into consideration for the company when making decisions on where to pursue action\nafter the models effectively predict churn.\n\n\n'

    # <u>Final Model Evaluation Selection

    In [210]:

    1
    """
    2
    3
    The final model selection that I went with was model 4 of the Random Rorest Classifier. It was a very close tie between the
    4
    4th model for Random Forest and the 4th model of XGBoost but ultimately, the Random Forest Classifier had better overall scores
    5
    towards the churn data. While the XGBoost model has a higher precision and f1 score compared to the Random Forest Classifier,
    6
    the primary score that is being focused on is recall. The trade off with a better recall score while having slightly lower
    7
    scores to the other metrics was worth choosing Random Forest as the final model.
    8
    9
    10
    """
